nsions. The crucial concept of the Female Baroque is developed in detail. Attention is then given particularly to Gertrude More, Mary Ward, Aemilia Lanyer, The Ferrar/Collet women, Mary Wroth, the Cavendish sisters, Hester Pulter, Anne Hutchinson, Margaret Cavendish and Aphra Behn, the latter two whose lives and writings point to the developing cultural transition to the Enlightenment.[-]  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aBaroque literaturexHistory and criticism. 0aEnglish literatureyEarly modern, 1500-1700xHistory and criticism. 0aWomen and literaturezEnglandxHistoryy17th century. 4aEarly Modern Studies. 4aGender and Sexuality Studies. 4aHistory, Art History, and Archaeology. 4aLiterary Theory, Criticism, and History. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Great Britain / Stuart Era (1603-1714).2bisacsh  aBaroque.  aFemale Baroque.  aJulia Kristeva.  aWomen's writing.  aearly modern England.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311068955608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2020 Part 2z978311069629508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2020 Englishz978311070473008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2020z9783110704525oZDB-23-DEG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPP ROW Ebook Package English 2020z978311069630140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048551118zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048551118423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789048551118/original  